I wonder <img src="https://cdn.artofproblemsolving.com/attachments/6/f/8370d9b7a3ca3f74c5b525f994dfbda6548d6.png" width="50"> this problem. Switch $$y$$ for $$2-3x$$ since that $$3x+y=2$$. Then, we can say that
\begin{align*}
13x&=9\\
x&=\frac{9}{13},
\end{align*}
and since $$y=2-3x$$, then
\begin{align*}
y&=2-3\cdot\left(\frac{9}{13}\right)\\
&=\frac{11}{13}\\
\end{align*}
So, $$5x-2y$$ is
\begin{align*}
5\cdot\left(\frac{9}{13}\right)-2\cdot\left(\frac{11}{13}\right)&=\frac{35}{13},
\end{align*}
and so, the line from this is already complete since
\begin{align*}
24x-14y&=2(12x-7y)\\
&=2(5-2y+y-y)\\
&=2(5-2y)\\
&=2(26-14y)\\
&=52y-26\\
&=42.
\end{align*}
</think> <answer>42</answer>

